<section id="pagehead">
	<h1>Alexis Horowitz-Burdick of Luxola on starting and growing an e-commerce business in southeast Asia</h1>
	<img src="/images/go/AlexisHorowitzBurdick.jpg" />
</section>

<section id="content">
<p>Alexis is founder and CEO of Luxola.com, which grew to become the largest online retailer for beauty products in Southeast Asia, more specifically in Singapore, Indonesia and Thailand.</p>

<p>In this interview, Alexis will describe in detail how she founded Luxola.com, how she markets beauty products in different countries, her hiring philosophies and how she raised money.</p>

<h3><a href="/downloads/AlexisHorowitzBurdick.mp3">download MP3</a></h3>

<h2>Highlights</h2>

<ul>
  <li>3:50: How did Alexis find her suppliers and how did she set up a distribution channel in Southeast Asia? What did she have to pay attention to when importing?</li>
  <li>6:55: The attraction of starting a business around physical products, specifically beauty products.</li>
  <li>10:50: How the unique way of doing customer service helped the company differentiate in Southeast Asia.</li>
  <li>16:00: What is the content strategy over different media for Luxola?</li>
  <li>19:45: How does Luxola market differently in Indonesia, Thailand and Singapore? Why does Luxola have different websites for each country?</li>
  <li>21:40: How Alexis build her team: how she hired in different countries and how her hiring philosophy evolved over time. The benefits of hiring in the countries she operates in.</li>
  <li>32:05: What is fundraising like for an eCommerce platform in Southeast Asia? What is her relationship with her investors?</li>
  <li>37:20: What exactly does Luxola use the raised funds for?</li>
  <li>40:05: What is the startup and investing scene in Singapore, Indonesia and Thailand like?</li>
  <li>45:35: The long term vision for Alexis.</li>
</ul>

